[src:chez-scheme/tail-call] One may need to introduce auxiliary variables or use a *swap* construct.
[src:chez-scheme/tail-call] Indeed, `n * factorial(n - 1)` wraps the call to `factorial`.
[src:chez-scheme/tail-call] But it can be transformed into a tail-recursive definition by adding an argument `a` called an *accumulator*.
